args:
After the Captain falls to Farren, he decides to
destroy the facility and take everyone with him.
In the midst of escaping the base as it goes up
in flames, Grace spots a person who seems to
be the leader of the entire Syndicateâ€”and that
mysterious stranger is none other than...
This is ridiculous... How am I losing?!
*pant* *pant* *pant* Stop this, Jake.\nThere's no point in our fighting any longer.
I don't need pity from a failed experiment!
I still think of you as my friend, Jake, and I\ncan't stand the idea of fighting a friend.
A friend? Aaaah ha ha ha! Oh, little duck!\nI was the one who sold you out!
You thought I sacrificed myself for you,\nbut I did the exact opposite!
After I volunteered to be taken in your\nplace, I told the Syndicate all about your\nlittle escape plan so they'd let me live.
THAT is the reality of the ï¼‚friendshipï¼‚\nyou so slavishly defend!
I know, Jake. I've always known.
One of the soldiers told me I'd been sold\nout after they caught me trying to escape.
And you still called me your friend?
Our friendship and your betrayal have\nnothing to do with each other.
On the day we met, you were the only\nperson who showed any concern for me.
Enough! I told you before that I don't need\nyour pity, and I sure as hell meant it!
I'm NOT Jake! I'm the Captain, one of the\nSyndicate's top brass!
To think that the Captain would fall so\neasily. I suppose this serves as further\nproof of your irregular power, Farren.
(The Overseer is one of the Syndicate's\nmajor bosses and one who supervises a\nnumber of bases...but why are they HERE?)

The Captain was thought indispensable to
the furtherance of the Wyrmbound Soldier
Project, so I came to oversee things in
case they somehow went awry.
But it seems my priorities were misplaced.\nClearly this irregular experiment is more\nworthy of saving than the Captain.
Oh no... Look how many wyrmbound\nare still left...
This ain't good, bucko. We're about outta\njuice here.
How fortunate that I can acquire both\nTf-997 and the irregular at the same time.
The Master will be most delighted.
Hear me, wyrmbound! The enemy has no\nstrength left. There's no need for tricks.\nJust take them outright!
So you've finally shown your ugly face,\neh, Overseer?
Your caution makes you hard to pin down,\nbut I knew you couldn't resist taking a peek\nat the Wyrmbound Soldier Project.
That's right. I've transcended your entire\nunderstanding of wyrmbinding.
Madness! None have taken the art of\nwyrmbinding further than we have.\nWho even are you?!
I am one with command over wyrmbinding,\nand I am the Syndicate's destruction.
I've come here to get all the information\nyou have on the Master.
I don't know who you are, but you forget\nthat you stand before all these wyrmbound.
Take him, my wyrmbound soldiers! We will\nwring every last drop of intelligence from\nhim once we have him in chains!
What...? He took them all out...
As I said, I have a mastery of wyrmbinding\nthat puts your skills to shame.
Ah, I see it now! You are the Doctor's...
Whether you know that or not, you can't\ndo a damned thing about it. Now let's hear\nabout the Master before... Huh?
Wait, he's fighting his own guys?\nI am VERY confused right now...

All of the Syndicate's top brass understand
that death is preferable to giving up
intelligence to our enemiesâ€”and that 
includes me.
I've activated the base's self-destruct\nmechanism, so I suggest running unless\nyou want this to be your tomb.
Sorry, little duck. But I'm a leader of the\nSyndicate, and I'm going to die that way.
But as my final act of revenge, I will force\nyou to live with the burden of your friend's\ndeath! Aaaah ha ha ha ha!
Uh, we need to get our butts outta\nhere yesterday!
Don't worry, I've got him. In fact, that was\none of my goals right from the start.
I think we can trust this guy, Grace.\n...I mean, you're the one who rescued me,\nright?
That's not really enough to trust you,\nbut I fear we've little time to spend\ndebating it.
Thank you for everything. We'll meet again\nsomeday, right?
If you're fighting the Syndicate, you'll\ndefinitely see me againâ€”whether you\nactually want to or not.
In that case, I'll leave Aldred to you.\nNow let's go!
It can't be... He can't be here!
This ain't no time to be standing around\ntakin' in the scenery, lady!
Yeah, next time you want to cut it close\nand make some grand exit, count me out!
Hey, we all made it, and that's what\nmatters. Now let's go back to the Halidom!
Is it truly all right for me to return\nto that place?
Care to fill us in on who?
Wait, you mean THE Master? Like, the\nbiggest and stinkiest of all the Syndicate\nbig cheeses?!
Indeed. And though this may be hard to\nbelieve, the Master is actually someone\nwe know well...
